Text:
Kratom to Suboxone? Dosage and questions, please help!. I know a lot of people might not like the fact I replaced kratom with suboxone, but I used to be taking 70 grams of kratom per day, I was dosing every 2-3 hours and practically carrying a pound of green powder everywhere I went. The suboxone lasts a whole day, and I can measure my dose way better since I'm taking the films.

&#x200B;

I started with quitting kratom completely and taking 2mg of suboxone, I experienced no withdrawals during the switch but also no high which is good i guess. Today I'm down to 1.5mg of suboxone, and im so happy! Planning to go down to 1.25mg pretty soon too. My question ig is exactly how many gpd of kratom is equal to 1.5mg of suboxone? I get its comparing apples to oranges but im hoping someone might have anecdotal advice.

&#x200B;

I was also wondering what suboxone withdrawal feels like at 1mg, 0.5mg and 0.25mg if I were to cold turkey at any of those dosages, what should I be expecting?

Nutrition help while in withdrawal. Hey Reddit I'm about to make my jump off 0.7mg subs tomorrow. It's a higher dose than I wanted to jump from but I got 2 weeks time off from work so the time is now. I have a box of Valium and Lyrica (thanks Mexico) to assist with getting rest, my mood, all that. I'm in a good place mentally and have an amazing support system. My problem is... 

&#x200B;

I'm a pretty skinny dude and have already lost some weight since I've been tapering, every drop in dose shot my appetite for a day or two. I really want to try to keep my weight loss to a minimum since I'm already down and it takes me so long to put it back on. I'd love to hear any advice y'all might have. Anything from supplements to exercise to what foods I should be eating, basically any advice on staying healthy and holding onto as much weight as possible through this process is what I'm looking for. Thanks in advance to everyone, you all have helped immensely over the last few months.
